A woman walks past a collection of medical workers' pictures at a subway station in Sao Paulo, Brazil, July 21, 2020. Brazil on Tuesday reported a total of 2,159,654 people have tested positive for COVID-19 and 81,487 patients have died from the disease. Brazil is one of the countries hardest hit by the pandemic, second only to the United States, both in terms of death toll and caseload. (Photo by Rahel Patrasso/Xinhua)Brazil on Tuesday reported a total of 2,159,654 people have tested positive for COVID-19 and 81,487 patients have died from the disease.In the past 24 hours, tests detected 41,008 new cases and 1,367 more patients died, the country's health ministry said.The southeast state of Sao Paulo, the country's most populous state, is the worst hit, with 422,669 cases and 20,171 deaths, followed by the neighboring state of Rio de Janeiro, with 145,121 cases and 12,293 deaths.Brazil is one of countries hardest hit by the pandemic, second only to the United States, both in terms of death toll and caseload. Massive changes to California voting spark fears of Iowa-style primary chaosAsian Americans wait for their turn to shine in HollywoodCal's epidemic protection services still have room for improvement